which, using 100,000 years, would put AOA beginning around 1k-2k years after the founding of vasselheim (equating vasselheim to mesopotamia, here) around the 12,800 years ago from 842PD

cause you have to factor in that there MIGHT not have been evolution and therefore you don't need 1mil years for elves to evolve into elves, etc., but it does follow the out of africa model since people "dispersed from vasselheim" at the end of the founding (start of AOA)

here is someone who understands magic in the same respect, so profoundly and limitless, but to advance knowledge and the expansion of their own horizons, rather than to harm or drag someone else down. true true kindred spirits, and i just loved that note in the comics.

and by extension, i think it is half the reason why essek found caleb so magnetizing in the first place. here are two broken people with nothing but a profound admiration and unbridled child-like wonder for the arcane and someone who completes that love without toxicity.

he has such an innocence when it comes to magic. to caleb, it's always a light, no matter what. yes the flames might bring back horrors, but the creation and expansion of magic is something that never leaves him, that never can be taken away.

despite the abuse and horror that he's gone through with eadwulf and astrid, caleb maintains this love for the arcane. its affirmed during the course of c2 when he makes his own spells, digs deep to find something that helps veth.

despite the horror of having crystals pressed into wounds of your arms, having to share body heat between three people to keep warm, caleb says how lovely the academy has been with such a wistful, longing look

its a very very small moment, but one that i think even is touched upon by liam/caleb in game. but, when caleb returns home after time at the academy, his parents ask him how he felt about his studies
